{{Infobox power station | name = Abertura Photovoltaic Power Station | name_official = Parque Fotovoltaico Abertura Solar | image = | image_size = | image_caption = | image_alt = | location_map = Spain | location_map_size = | location_map_caption = | coordinates = {{coord|39.226|-5.779|type:landmark_region:ES|display=inline,title}} | coordinates_ref = | country = Abertura, [[Province of Cáceres|Cáceres]] | location = [[Spain]] | status = O | construction_began = | commissioned = | decommissioned = | cost = | owner = | operator = [[Iberdrola]] | solar_type = PV | solar_cpv_concentration = | solar_csp_heliostats = | solar_cpvt = | solar_site_area = | ps_electrical_capacity = 23.1 [[Megawatt|MW]] | website = | extra = }} '''Abertura Photovoltaic Power Station''' ({{lang-es|Parque Fotovoltaico Abertura Solar}}) is a [[photovoltaic power station]] in the municipality of Abertura, [[Province of Cáceres|Cáceres]] in [[Spain]]. It has a total capacity of 23.1&nbsp;MWp.<ref>[http://www.exenewable.com/projectProfile.asp?id=12614 eXenewable Project Profile Page - Abertura, PV, Spain] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101031063643/http://www.exenewable.com/projectProfile.asp?id=12614 |date=October 31, 2010 }}</ref> The solar park was built by Iberinco. Double axes solar trackers were provided by Mecasolar and Inspira. The financing consortium was led by [[West LB]], [[Bank of Scotland]] and [[Dexia]]. A technical advisor was Sylcom Solar.
